'''Adolf Fischbach''' (5 August 1920 – 16 November 1972) was an [[Oberleutnant]] in the [[Luftwaffe]] during [[World War II]], and a recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership.
==Awards and decorations== * [[Aviator badge]] * [[Front Flying Clasp of the Luftwaffe]] * [[Ehrenpokal der Luftwaffe]] (20 December 1941) * [[Iron Cross]] (1939) ** 2nd Class ** 1st Class * [[German Cross]] in Gold (24 September 1942) * [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] on 3 September 1943 as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' and ''[[Staffelkapitän]]'' of the 4./Kampfgeschwader 27 "Boelcke"<ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 151.</ref>
